The graph shows the line $y = 2x - 1$ with four points marked. Which point lies on the line?
[tikz]
 egin{tikzpicture} egin{axis}[width=6.4cm,height=5.8cm,axis lines=middle,axis line style={-{Stealth}},xmin=-1,xmax=4,ymin=-2,ymax=6,xtick={-1,0,1,2,3,4},ytick={-2,0,2,4,6},grid=both,clip=false,scaled ticks=false,ticklabel style={font=\small,/pgf/number format/fixed},xlabel={$x$},ylabel={$y$}]\addplot[thick,<->,domain=-0.3:3.3,samples=2] {2*x-1};\addplot[only marks,mark=*,mark size=2.2pt] coordinates {(0,1) (1,2) (2,3) (3,4)};
ode[above right] at (axis cs:0,1) {$A$};
ode[above left] at (axis cs:1,2) {$B$};
ode[below right] at (axis cs:2,3) {$C$};
ode[below right] at (axis cs:3,4) {$D$};\end{axis}\end{tikzpicture}
[/tikz]
